Comment: Hi everyone!  his is a game I played a few years back in the Foxwoods Open.  This game was played against someone with a rating more than 500 pts higher than me at the time.  I ended up losing this game, but I wanted to share it because it is by far the best game I have ever played in a tournament setting.

This move characterizes the Zietzef variation of the lopez.  It can be a very sharp, tactical middlegame.  The reason I played it aganst someone so much higher than me is because he showed up almost an hour late for his match!!  I was going to try to make things as difficult as possible.
